{"award_age":33.0,"bio_image":"full\/e26cce92ea361023ecb900b28448af23806f966f.jpg","category":"Physics","country":"United Kingdom","date_of_birth":"1940-01-04T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/f\/ff\/Brian_Josephson%2C_March_2004.jpg\/220px-Brian_Josephson%2C_March_2004.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson","mini_bio":"<p><b>Brian David Josephson<\/b>, <span style=\"font-size:85%;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FRS<\/a><\/span> (born 4 January 1940), is a Welsh theoretical physicist and professor emeritus of physics at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Cambridge\" title=\"University of Cambridge\">University of Cambridge<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Best known for his pioneering work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Superconductivity\" title=\"Superconductivity\">superconductivity<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_tunnelling\" title=\"Quantum tunnelling\">quantum tunnelling<\/a>, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel Prize in Physics<\/a> in 1973 for his prediction of the eponymous <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Josephson_effect\" title=\"Josephson effect\">Josephson effect<\/a>, made in 1962 when he was a 22-year-old PhD student at Cambridge. Josephson is the only Welsh person to have won a Nobel Prize in Physics. He shared the prize with physicists <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Leo_Esaki\" title=\"Leo Esaki\">Leo Esaki<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ivar_Giaever\" title=\"Ivar Giaever\">Ivar Giaever<\/a>, who jointly received half the award for their own work on quantum tunnelling.<sup id=\"cite_ref-britannica_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson#cite_note-britannica-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>Josephson has spent his academic career as a member of the Theory of Condensed Matter group at Cambridge's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cavendish_Laboratory\" title=\"Cavendish Laboratory\">Cavendish Laboratory<\/a>. He has been a fellow of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Trinity_College,_Cambridge\" title=\"Trinity College, Cambridge\">Trinity College<\/a> since 1962, and served as professor of physics from 1974 until 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-britannica_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson#cite_note-britannica-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In the early 1970s Josephson took up <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Transcendental_meditation\" title=\"Transcendental meditation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">transcendental meditation<\/a> and turned his attention to issues outside the parameters of mainstream science. He set up the Mind\u2013Matter Unification Project at the Cavendish to explore the idea of intelligence in nature, the relationship between <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_mechanics\" title=\"Quantum mechanics\">quantum mechanics<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Consciousness\" title=\"Consciousness\">consciousness<\/a>, and the synthesis of science and Eastern mysticism, broadly known as <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Quantum_mysticism\" title=\"Quantum mysticism\">quantum mysticism<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Those interests have led him to express support for topics such as <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Parapsychology\" title=\"Parapsychology\">parapsychology<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Water_memory\" title=\"Water memory\">water memory<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cold_fusion\" title=\"Cold fusion\">cold fusion<\/a>, and have made him a focus of criticism from fellow scientists.<sup id=\"cite_ref-britannica_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Brian_David_Josephson#cite_note-britannica-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Brian David Josephson","place_of_birth":"Cardiff, Wales","place_of_death":null,"text":"Brian David Josephson , Physics, 1973","year":1973.0}